#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "Peripheral devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Below this percentage, the battery charge for peripheral devices &eg; a "
"wireless mouse will be considered low."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid "Charge Limit"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These settings are only displayed if the system supports charge limits for "
"its battery."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regularly charging the battery close to 100% or fully discharging it close "
"to 0% can cause it to deteriorate faster. By limiting the maximum battery "
"charge, you can help extend your battery's lifespan."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Different sources recommend different charge levels for lithium-ion "
"batteries. The general consensus among available research indicates that "
"keeping your battery within the 25%-75% range is optimal to retain its "
"capacity over the years. A range of 15%-85% still significantly increases "
"battery life compared to wider ranges."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that battery lifespan is mainly affected by its charge level over time, "
"more so than the number of charging and discharging cycles."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:266
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stop charging at"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The upper charge limit for your battery. Once this level is reached, the "
"battery is considered fully charged and the system won't charge it any "
"further."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:272
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start charging once below"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The lower charge limit. Once the battery discharges past this level, the "
"system will start charging it again. This can be a little lower than the "
"upper limit, or the same percentage to keep drawing power while the battery "
"charge remains constant."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:280
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some systems require unplugging the power cable and reconnecting it before "
"the settings are respected. Some systems don't store charge limits when "
"powered off. Be aware of possible limitations."
msgstr ""

